 (Sweden, Germany, France, Italy, Spain and Portugal); in its focus on the actual working of their policies: their set of actors; cultural background; implementation etc. and in its methodological approach, which combines longitudinal analysis with qualitative research. Academics and students of welfare and poverty, policy makers and social policy evaluators in the public, private and non profit sectors will find this book invaluable.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aPublic welfarezEurope. 0aSocial actionzEurope. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Services & Welfare.2bisacsh1 aBonny, Yves, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBosco, Nicoletta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarcia, Marisol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGustafsson, Björn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKazepov, Yuri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMingione, Enzo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Rolf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNegri, Nicola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOberti, Marco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPereirinha, José, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaraceno, Chiara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaraceno, Chiara, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aVoges, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z978311119621340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/97818